    <section id="results" class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Experimental Results</p>
      <h2>What we found</h2>
      <p>All four models were evaluated on the same held-out test set (20 samples, stratified).</p>

      <div class="math-section">
        <h3 class="sub-title">Evaluation Metrics</h3>
        <p>We report four standard binary classification metrics. Let TP = true positive (AD correctly detected), TN = true negative (healthy correctly identified), FP = false positive (healthy misclassified as AD), FN = false negative (AD missed):</p>
        <div class="metric-formulas">
          <div class="metric-formula-card">
            <p class="metric-name">Accuracy</p>
            <div class="math-display" is:raw>$$\text{Accuracy} = \frac{TP + TN}{TP + TN + FP + FN}$$</div>
            <p class="metric-note">Overall fraction of correct predictions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="metric-formula-card">
            <p class="metric-name">Precision</p>
            <div class="math-display" is:raw>$$\text{Precision} = \frac{TP}{TP + FP}$$</div>
            <p class="metric-note">Of all AD predictions, how many are real AD cases.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="metric-formula-card">
            <p class="metric-name">Recall (Sensitivity)</p>
            <div class="math-display" is:raw>$$\text{Recall} = \frac{TP}{TP + FN}$$</div>
            <p class="metric-note">Of all real AD cases, how many we detected. Critical for clinical screening.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="metric-formula-card">
            <p class="metric-name">F1-Score</p>
            <div class="math-display" is:raw>$$F_1 = 2 \cdot \frac{\text{Precision} \cdot \text{Recall}}{\text{Precision} + \text{Recall}} = \frac{2\,TP}{2\,TP + FP + FN}$$</div>
            <p class="metric-note">Harmonic mean of precision and recall. Robust to class imbalance.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="math-note">With 76 healthy vs 55 AD samples, pure accuracy is misleading (a "predict healthy always" classifier would score 58%). We prioritize <em>recall</em> for clinical relevance: missing an AD patient is far more costly than a false alarm.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Model</th>
              <th>Accuracy</th>
              <th>Precision</th>
              <th>Recall</th>
              <th>F1-Score</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="row-best">
              <td><strong>SVM</strong> <span class="badge">Best</span></td>
              <td><strong>75.0%</strong></td>
              <td><strong>71.4%</strong></td>
              <td>62.5%</td>
              <td><strong>66.7%</strong></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>CNN</td>
              <td>70.0%</td>
              <td>62.5%</td>
